 topic|1930 in}}\n[[Category:1930 in China]]\n[[Category:1930s in China]]\n[[Category:Years of the 20th century in China]]\n", "text_old": "{{Year in China|1930}}\nEvents from the year '''1930 in China'''.\n\n==Incumbents==\n*[[President of the Republic of China|President]]: [[Chiang Kai-shek]] \n*[[Premier of the Republic of China|Premier]]: \n** until September 22: [[Tan Yankai]] \n** 25 September-4 December: [[Soong Tse-ven]]\n** starting 4 December: [[Chiang Kai-shek]]\n*[[List of vice premiers of the Republic of China|Vice Premier]]: [[Feng Yuxiang]] until October 11, [[Soong Tse-ven]]\n\n==Events==\n* 29 January - 24 March: [[Encirclement Campaign against Hunan\u2013Jiangxi Soviet]]\n* 2 March: The [[League of the Left-Wing Writers]] was established in [[Shanghai]], at the instigation of the [[Chinese Communist Party]] and the influence of the celebrated author [[Lu Xun]]. \n* May \u2013 4 November: [[Central Plains War]]\n* 6 May: The [[Republic of China|China]] signed tariff treaties with Japan. The Republic of China government obtained itself right of tariff autonomy. Some Japanese goods do not need to pay tariffs.\n* 27 October - 1 December: [[Musha incident]] in Taiwan.\n* December - [[Futian incident]]\n\n==Births==\n*January 1 - [[Sihung Lung]], actor (died [[2002 in China|2002]])\n*June - [[Li Zehou]], philosopher\n*June 10 - [[Chen Xitong]], politician (died [[2013 in China|2013]])\n*December 30 - [[Tu Youyou]], pharmaceutical chemist\n*''date unknown''\n**[[Hua Sanchuan]], painter and illustrator (died [[2004 in China|2004]])\n**[[Wu Yen-hsia]], t'ai chi ch'uan teacher (died [[2001 in China|2001]])\n\n==Deaths==\n*February 24 - [[Wang Zuo]] and [[Yuan Wencai]], bandit leaders (assassinated)\n*November 14 - [[Yang Kaihui]], second wife of [[Mao Zedong]] (born [[1901 in China|1901]]; executed)<ref>Chang, Jung; Halliday, Jon (2005). Mao: The Unknown Story. London: Jonathan Cape. {{ISBN|978-0-224-07126-0}}.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==See a