ia Valke]]\n |score= \u2013\n |away= [[China Lions]]\n |report= \n |try1= \n |con1= \n |pen1= \n |cards1= \n |try2= \n |con2= \n |pen2= \n |card2= \n |stadium= Stadium {{abbr|TUDM|Tentera Udara Diraja Malaysia}}, Subang\n |attendance= \n |referee= \n}}\n\n=== Round 3 ===\nAll competition matches suspended.\n{{rugbybox collapsible |class=collapsible expanded |note-width=0 |date-width=18% |stadium-width=22% \n |date= 28 March\n |time= {{resize|90%|3.15 pm [[Fiji Standard Time|FJT]] ([[UTC+12:00|UTC+12]])}}\n |home= [[Fijian Latui]] \n |score= \u2013\n |away= [[Western Force]]\n |report= \n |try1= \n |con1= \n |pen1= \n |cards1= \n |try2= \n |con2= \n |pen2= \n |card2= \n |stadium= [[Churchill Park (Lautoka)|Churchill Park]], Lautoka\n |attendance= \n |referee= \n}} \n\n{{rugbybox collapsible |class=collapsible expanded |note-width=0 |date-width=18% |stadium-width=22% \n |date= 28 March\n |time= {{resize|90%|4.15 pm [[Time in Malaysia|MYT]] ([[UTC+08:00|UTC+8]])}}\n |home= [[Malaysia Valke]] \n |score= \u2013\n |away= [[Manuma Samoa]] \n |report= \n |try1= \n |con1= \n |pen1= \n |cards1= \n |try2= \n |con2= \n |pen2= \n |card2= \n |stadium= Stadium {{abbr|TUDM|Tentera Udara Diraja Malaysia}}, Subang\n |attendance= \n |referee= \n}}\n\n{{rugbybox collapsible |class=collapsible expanded |note-width=0 |date-width=18% |stadium-width=22% \n |date= 29 March\n |time= {{resize|90%|3.15 pm [[Time in New Zealand|NZDT]] ([[UTC+13:00|UTC+13]])}}\n |home= [[China Lions]] \n |score= \u2013\n |away= [[South China Tigers]] \n |report= \n |try1= \n |con1= \n |pen1= \n |cards1= \n |try2= \n |con2= \n |pen2= \n |card2= \n |stadium= [[Owen Delany Park]], Taupo\n |attendance= \n |referee= \n}} \n\n{| cellspacing=0 style=\"border-top:0px solid 000000; border-bottom:1px solid #e0e0e0; width: {{{size|100%}}}\"\n|-\n| style=\"width:100%; text-align:center; vertical-align:top; font-size:85%;\"| ''There {{show by date|2020|04|06|is|was}} a competition bye for the weekend of 3\u20135 April.''\n|}