id Rugby and South China Tigers coming to Hong Kong for two games in 2019\n |work=South China Morning Post\n |url=https://www.scmp.com/print/sport/rugby/article/2188180/global-rapid-rugby-and-south-china-tigers-coming-hong-kong-two-games\n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190309080552/https://www.scmp.com/print/sport/rugby/article/2188180/global-rapid-rugby-and-south-china-tigers-coming-hong-kong-two-games\n |archivedate=9 March 2019\n}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.rapidrugby.com/ Rapid Rugby] official website\n* [http://www.asierugby.net/transferts-global-rapid-rugby-2020.php 2020 player transfers] at asierugby.net\n\n{{Global Rapid Rugby}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Asian rugby union|Global Rapid Rugby]]\n[[Category:2020 in Oceanian rugby union|Global Rapid Rugby]]\n[[Category:2020 in Australian rugby union|Global Rapid Rugby]]\n[[Category:Current rugby union seasons|Global Rapid Rugby]]\n[[Category:Sports events postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|Global Rapid Rugby]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox sports season\n| title              = 2020 Rapid Rugby Season\n| color              = #242060\n| color_text         = white\n| sport              = [[rugby union|Rugby]]\n| league             = [[Global Rapid Rugby]]\n| duration           = 13 March \u2013 6 June\n| no_of_matches      = 31\n| no_of_teams        = 6 \n| attendance         =\n| average_attendance =\n| league_champ_name  = Winner\n| league_champs      = <!--[[Western Force]]-->\n| prevseason_year    = 2019 |prevseason_link = 2019 Global Rapid Rugby season\n| nextseason_year    = 2021 |nextseason_link = {{show by date|2021|01|01||2021 Global Rapid Rugby season}}\n}}\n\nThe 2020 season {{show by date|2020|06|07|is|was}} the first [[Global Rapid Rugby]] home and away tournament and {{show by date|2020|06|07|follows|followed}} the shorter showcase series held the previous year.<ref name=scmp-1-mar-2019/> It {{show by date|2020|06|07|is|was}} a [[rugby union]] competition featuring six teams from across the [[Asia-Pacific]] region. The tournament {{show by date|2020|06|07|is|was}} capped by a grand final match between the top two teams with a [[Australian dollar|A$]]1 million prize for the winner.\n\nAfter only one completed round of competition, Global Rapid Rugby announced on 15 March 2020, that the season would be suspended immediately because of travel, quarantine and public health restrictions due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 season suspnded |url=https://www.rapid.rugby/2020-season-suspended/ |website=Rapid Rugby |accessdate=15 March 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315090857/https://www.rapid.rugby/2020-season-suspended/ |archivedate=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{toc level|3}}\n\n==Teams==\nThe following six teams were announced for the Rapid Rugby season in 2020:{{hsp}}<ref name=\"sched-2020\">{{cite web\n |title=Season One\n |url=https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/rapid.rugby-assets/content/uploads/2020/02/28170851/2020-Global-Rapid-Rugby-Schedule-February-28-2020_-768x1077.jpg\n |website=amazon.aws\n |publisher=Rapid Rugby\n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229050448/https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/rapid.rugby-assets/content/uploads/2020/02/28170851/2020-Global-Rapid-Rugby-Schedule-February-28-2020_-768x1077.jpg\n |archivedate=29 February 2020\n |date=28 February 2020\n}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|- style=\"color:white;\"\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#242060;\"| Team\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#242060;\"| City\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#242060;\"| Stadium\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#242060;\"| Capacity\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#242060;\"| Head coach\n|-\n|{{flagicon|CHN}} [[China Lions]]{{hsp}}{{efn|name=\"Samoa\"\n|The China Lions, backed by the [[Chinese Rugby Football Association|China Rugby Football Association]] and New Zealand's [[Bay of Plenty Rugby Union]], were originally scheduled to host three of their home games in Shanghai. One of those fixtures was moved to Taupo in New Zealand and the other two to Adelaide in Australia due to health concerns relating to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=\"sched-2020\"/><ref>{{cite web\n |title=All systems go for Global Rapid Rugby\n |url=https://www.rapid.rugby/all-systems-go-for-global-rapid-rugby/\n |website=Rapid Rugby\n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226014759/https://www.rapid.rugby/all-systems-go-for-global-rapid-rugby/\n |archivedate=26 February 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"ys-feb-2020\">{{cite web\n |last1=Chadwick |first1=Justin\n |title=Global Rapid Rugby won't travel to China |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225192802/https://au.sports.yahoo.com/global-rapid-rugby-wont-travel-china-081325263--spt.html\n |website=Yahoo\n |archiveurl=https://au.sports.yahoo.com/global-rapid-rugby-wont-travel-china-081325263--spt.html\n |archivedate=25 February 2020\n |date=25 February 2020\n}}</ref>}}\n|[[Rotorua]]<hr>[[Taupo]]<hr>[[Adelaide]]\n|[[Rotorua International Stadium]]<hr>[[Owen Delany Park]]<hr>[[Hindmarsh Stadium|Coopers Stadium]]\n|align=center|34,000<hr>20,000<hr>16,500\n|[[Mike Rogers (rugby union)|Mike Rogers]]{{hsp}}<ref name=\"ra247--5-mar-2020\">{{cite web |title=China Lions play warmup GRR game |url=https://www.rugbyasia247.com/china-lions-play-warmup-grr-game/ |website=Rugby Asia 24/7 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306010310/https://www.rugbyasia247.com/china-lions-play-warmup-grr-game/ |archivedate=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2| {{flagicon|FIJ}} [[Fijian Latui]]\n|[[Suva]]\n|[[ANZ National Stadium|ANZ Stadium]] <hr> [[Albert Park (Suva)|Albert Park]]\n|align=center|15,000 <hr> 3,000\n|rowspan=2| [[Senirusi Seruvakula]]\n|-\n|[[Lautoka]]<hr>[[Nausori]]\n|[[Churchill Park (Lautoka)|Churchill Park]] <hr> [[Ratu Cakobau Park]]\n|align=center|9,500 <hr> 8,000\n|-\n|{{flagicon|SAM}} [[Manuma Samoa]]\n|[[Apia]]\n|[[Apia Park]] \n|align=center|12,000\n|[[Brian Lima]]{{hsp}}<ref>{{cite news  |date=21 November 2019 |last1=Airey |first1=Thomas |title=Manum\u0101 the \"missing link\" to get locals to Manu Samoa  |work=Samoa Observer |url=https://www.samoaobserver.ws/category/sport/53583 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122042436/https://www.samoaobserver.ws/category/sport/53583 |archivedate=22 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|MAS}} [[Malaysia Valke]] \n|[[Kuala Lumpur]]<hr>[[Subang, Selangor|Subang]]\n|[[Bukit Jalil National Stadium]]<hr>[[Stadium TUDM]]\n|align=center|87,411<hr>6,000\n|[[Rudy Joubert]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|HKG}} [[South China Tigers]]\n|[[Hong Kong]]\n|[[Hong Kong Stadium]]<hr>[[Siu Sai Wan Sports Ground]]<hr>[[Aberdeen Sports Ground]]<!--<hr>[[Mong Kok Stadium]]-->\n|align=center|40,000 <hr> 11,981 <hr> 9,000 <!--<hr> 6,769-->\n|[[Craig Hammond]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Western Force]]\n|[[Perth]]\n|[[Perth Oval|HBF Park]]\n|align=center|20,500\n|[[Tim Sampson]]\n|}\n\n;Notes\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Standings==\nA modified version of the [[rugby union bonus points system|rugby bonus points system]] {{show by date|2020|05|25|is|was}} used for the regular season. One bonus point {{show by date|2020|05|25|is|was}} awarded for each of the following in a game:<ref>{{cite web |title=Points plus |url=https://www.rapidrugby.com/rapid-rugby/ |website=Rapid Rugby |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321141700/https://www.rapid.rugby/rapid-rugby/ |archivedate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n* a team scoring 4 or more tries;\n* a winning team scoring at least 3 tries more than their opponent; \n* a team defeated by a margin of 5 points or under.\n\nFour points {{show by date|2020|05|25|are|were}} awarded for a win and none for a loss<!--or bye-->. Two points {{show by date|2020|05|25|are|were}} awarded to each team for a draw.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:80%; text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"100%\" style=\"background:#242060;| [[Global Rapid Rugby|{{color|white|Global Rapid Rugby}}]]\n|-\n! style=\"width:1em;\" | #\n! style=\"width:9.5em;\" | Team\n! style=\"width:1em;\" | {{abbr| P | Games played}}\n! style=\"width:1em;\" | {{abbr| W | Games won}}\n! style=\"width:1em;\" | {{abbr| D | Games drawn}}\n! style=\"width:1em;\" | {{abbr| L | Games lost}} <!-- comment out\n! style=\"width:1.5em;\" | {{abbr| PF | Points for}}\n! style=\"width:1.5em;\" | {{abbr| PA | Points against}} -->\n! style=\"width:1.5em;\" | {{abbr| PD | Points difference}}\n! style=\"width:1.5em;\" | {{abbr| TF | Tries for}}\n! style=\"width:1.5em;\" | {{abbr| TA | Tries against}}\n! style=\"width:1em;\" | {{abbr| TB | Try bonus points}}\n! style=\"width:1em;\" | {{abbr| LB | Losing bonus points}}\n! style=\"width:1em;\" | {{abbr| Pts| Total points}}\n<!--\n|# || Team\n| P || W || D || L ||  PF   ||  PA ||     PD  || TF || TA || TB|| LB|| Pts -->\n|-\n|1 || style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Western Force]]\n| 1 || 1 || 0 || 0 ||<!-- 51 ||  1 ||-->  +37 ||  7 ||  2 || 2 || 0 || '''6'''\n|-\n|2 || style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{flagicon|HKG}} [[South China Tigers]]\n| 1 || 1 || 0 || 0 ||<!-- 52 || 27 ||-->  +25 ||  8 ||  3 || 2 || 0 || '''6'''\n|-\n|3 || style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{flagicon|CHN}} [[China Lions]]\n| 1 || 1 || 0 || 0 ||<!--  29 ||  22||-->  +7 ||  4 ||  3 || 1 || 0 || '''5'''\n|-\n|4 || style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{flagicon|FIJ}} [[Fijian Latui]]\n| 1 || 0 || 0 || 1 ||<!--  22 ||  29||-->  \u20137 ||  3 ||  4 || 0 || 0 || '''0'''\n|-\n|5 || style=\"text-align:left;\" |  {{flagicon|SAM}} [[Manuma Samoa]]\n| 1 || 0 || 0 || 1 ||<!--  27 ||  52||--> \u201325 ||  3 ||  8 || 0 || 0 || '''0'''\n|-\n|6 || style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{flagicon|MAS}} [[Malaysia Valke]]\n| 1 || 0 || 0 || 1 ||<!--  14 ||  51||--> \u201337 ||  2 ||  7 || 0 || 0 || '''0'''\n|-\n| colspan=\"100%\" style=\"border:0;\"|<small>'''Updated: 15 March 2020''' <br />\nSource: [https://www.rapidrugby.com/fixtures/ rapidrugby.com]\n|}\n\n== Regular season ==\nThe schedule was announced in February 2020.<ref name=\"sched-2020\"/>\n\n=== Round 1 ===\n{{rugbybox collapsible |note-width=0 |date-width=18% |stadium-width=22%\n |date= 14 March\n |time= {{resize|90%|6.15 pm [[Fiji Standard Time|FJT]] ([[UTC+12:00|UTC+12]])}}\n |home= [[Fijian Latui]]\n |score= 22\u201329\n |away= [[China Lions]]\n |report= Report<ref>{{cite web |title=Lions surprise Fiji in season-opener |url=https://www.rapid.rugby/lions-surprise-fiji-in-season-opener/ |website=Rapid Rugby |date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n |try1= [[Eremasi Radroro|Radroro]]<br />[[Lepani Raiyala|Raiyala]]<br />[[Apisalome Vota|Vota]]\n |con1= [[Teti Tela|Tela]] (2/3)\n |pen1= [[Teti Tela|Tela]] (1/1)\n |cards1=\n |try2= [[Fa'asui Fuatai|Fuatai]]<br />[[Penalty try]]<br />[[Ray Tatafu|Tatafu]], [[James Little (rugby union)|Little]] \n |con2= [[Dan Hollinshead|Hollinshead]] (3/3)\n |pen2= [[Dan Hollinshead|Hollinshead]] (1/1)\n |card2=\n |stadium= [[ANZ National Stadium|ANZ Stadium]], Suva\n |attendance=\n |referee= Cam Stone ({{Runion|NZL}})<!--Richard Kelly (New Zealand), Tevita Rokovereni (Fiji)\nTelevision match official: Jonathan Paterson (New Zealand), Assessor: Greg Hinton (Malaysia)-->{{hsp}}<ref name=\"rd1-officials\">{{cite web |last1=Dobson |first1=Paul |title=Referees to 16 March 2020 |url=https://rugby365.com/countries/argentina/referees-to-16-march-2020 |website=Rugby 365 |archivedate=11 March 2020 |date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{rugbybox collapsible |note-width=0 |date-width=18% |stadium-width=22%\n |date= 14 March\n |time= {{resize|90%|4.10 pm [[Australian Western Standard Time|AWST]] ([[UTC+08:00|UTC+8]])}}\n |home= [[Manuma Samoa]]\n |score= 27\u201352\n |away= [[South China Tigers]]\n |report= Report<ref>{{cite web |title=Tigers secure win with late charge |url=https://www.rapid.rugby/tigers-secure-win-with-late-charge/ |website=Rapid Rugby |date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n |try1= [[Oneone Soisoi|Soisoi]] (2, one pwt)<br />[[Alofaaga Sao|Sao]]\n |con1= [[D'Angelo Leuila|Leuila]] (1/2)\n |pen1= [[D'Angelo Leuila|Leuila]] (2/2)\n |cards1=\n |try2= [[Josh Dowsing|Dowsing]] (2)<br />[[George Watkins (rugby union)|Watkins]], [[Nathan De Thierry|De Thierry]] (2)<br />[[Mark Prior (rugby union)|Prior]], [[Luke van de Smit|Van de Smit]]<br />[[Callum McFeat Smith|McFeat Smith]]\n |con2= [[Glyn Hughes (rugby union)|Hughes]] (6/8)\n |pen2=\n |card2=\n |stadium= [[Perth Oval|HBF Park]], Perth\n |attendance=\n |referee= [[Nick Briant]] ({{Runion|NZL}})<!--Assistant referees: Mark Sheriff (Australia), Jordan Kaminski (Australia), Television match official: Kyle Burnett (Australia), Assessor: Hugh Watkins (Hong Kong)-->{{hsp}}<ref name=\"rd1-officials\"/>\n}}\n\n{{rugbybox collapsible |note-width=0 |date-width=18% |stadium-width=22%\n |date= 14 March\n |time= {{resize|90%|6.15 pm [[Australian Western Standard Time|AWST]] ([[UTC+08:00|UTC+8]])}}\n |home= [[Western Force]]\n |score= 51\u201314\n |away= [[Malaysia Valke]]\n |report= Report<ref>{{cite web |title=Western Force dominant in Rapid Rugby opener |url=https://www.rapid.rugby/western-force-dominant-in-rapid-rugby-opener/ |website=Rapid Rugby |date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n |try1= [[Brad Lacey|Lacey]] (2)<br />[[Marcel Brache|Brache]], [[Henry Taefu|Taefu]] pwt<br />[[Johan Bardoul|Bardoul]], [[Jack McGregor|McGregor]]<br />[[Chris Alcock|Alcock]]\n |con1= [[Ian Prior (rugby union)|Prior]] (6/6)\n |pen1=\n |cards1=\n |try2= [[Errol Jaggers|Jaggers]]<br />[[Valentino Wellman|Wellman]]\n |con2= [[Divan Nel|Nel]] (2/2)\n |pen2=\n |card2=\n |stadium= [[Perth Oval|HBF Park]], Perth\n |attendance=\n |referee= Tim Baker ({{Runion|HKG}})<!--Assistant referees: Matt Rodden (Hong Kong), Sam Jones (Australia), Television match official: Kyle Burnett (Australia), Assessor: Chris Pollock (New Zealand)-->{{hsp}}<ref name=\"rd1-officials\"/>\n}}\n\n=== Round 2 ===\nAll competition matches suspended.\n{{rugbybox collapsible |note-width=0 |da