hardly play in the match from summer 2005.<ref>[https://data.j-league.or.jp/SS/jpn/team/2005010001_000010_W0707_J.html J.League]</ref> In 2006, he moved to J2 club [[Vissel Kobe]]. He played many matches and Vissel was promoted to J1 end of [[2006 J.League Division 2|2006 season]]. In 2007, he was converted to side back and played many matches as right and left side back. Although he could hardly play in the match for injury in 2008, he played as regular player as side back from 2009. However Vissel was relegated to J2 end of [[2012 J.League Division 1|2012 season]]. Although Vissel was returned to J1 end od [[2013 J.League Division 1|2013 season]], his opportunity to play decreased from 2013. In 2015, he returned to his local and joined [[J3 League]] club [[Fukushima United FC]].<ref>[http://fufc.jp/news_cat/201501091500 Fukushima United FC]{{in lang|ja}}</ref> He played many matches as forward and side back every season. He retired end of 201 season.<ref>[http://fufc.jp/news_cat/201901051300 Fukushima United FC]{{in lang|ja}}</ref>\n\n==National team career==\nIn September 2001, Mogi was selected [[Japan national under-17 football team|Japan U-17 national team]] for [[2001 FIFA U-17 World Championship|2001 U-17 World Championship]]. He played as forward in all 3 matches. In November 2003, he was also selected [[Japan national under-20 football team|Japan U-20 national team]] for [[2003 FIFA World Youth Championship|2003 World Youth Championship]]. He played as forward in all 5 matches.\n\n==Club statistics==\n<ref>[http://fufc.jp/news_cat/201901051300 Fukushima United FC]{{in lang|ja}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Club performance\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | Cup\n! colspan=2 | League Cup\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! Season !! Club !! League\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Japan\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | [[Emperor's Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | [[J.Leag